    "content": "<div class=\"answer-block\"><strong>Quick answer:</strong> To share a PDF business card on WhatsApp, open the chat, tap the attach (paperclip or plus) icon, choose Document, select your card PDF, and send. The receiver taps to open it and can immediately use the call, WhatsApp, UPI and social buttons inside, no app or internet needed to view.</div>\n<p>WhatsApp is where India does business, so it is the perfect place to share your card. The trick to sharing a <strong>PDF business card on WhatsApp</strong> is sending it as a Document, not as a photo, so every button stays tappable and your card works exactly as designed.</p>\n<p>Send it as an image and the links die, leaving a pretty picture that does nothing. Send it as a document and every call, chat and UPI button works on the first tap.</p>\n<p>This guide covers the exact steps on Android and iPhone, why the Document choice matters, and smart ways to reach many people at once without extra effort.</p>\n<h2>How do I send a PDF card on WhatsApp step by step?</h2>\n<p>The process takes under ten seconds once your card is saved to your phone. If you received your MyCarda file by email or download, save it to your phone first so it is ready in your files.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Open the <strong>WhatsApp chat</strong> with the person you want to reach</li>\n<li>Tap the <strong>attach icon</strong> (paperclip on iPhone, plus or clip on Android)</li>\n<li>Choose <strong>Document</strong>, not Gallery or Photos</li>\n<li>Find and select your <strong>MyCarda PDF file</strong></li>\n<li>Tap <strong>Send</strong></li>\n</ol>\n<p>The receiver taps the file to open it and can immediately use the interactive buttons. Add a short line like \"Here is my card, tap any button to reach me\" so they know it is more than a picture. If you are new to these cards, start with <a href=\"/blog/what-is-pdf-digital-business-card\">what is a PDF digital business card</a> to understand what the buttons do.</p>\n<h2>Why must I send it as a Document, not a photo?</h2>\n<p>This is the single most important tip on this page. WhatsApp compresses photos to save data, and that process strips out the clickable links, leaving a flat image where nothing is tappable. Many people share their card as a photo without realising it, then wonder why customers still type their number by hand.</p>\n<p>Sending as a <strong>Document</strong> preserves the PDF exactly as designed. Every link survives, so <strong>click-to-call, WhatsApp, the UPI QR and your social buttons</strong> all stay live. The file also keeps its full quality, so text stays crisp and your logo does not turn blurry.</p>\n<p>Before you hit send, glance at the option you tapped and confirm it says Document. That one check is the difference between a card that works and one that just sits there. See how the buttons are built on our <a href=\"/how-it-works\">how it works</a> page.</p>\n<h2>How can I share my card with many people at once?</h2>\n<p>You do not have to send it one chat at a time. WhatsApp gives you several ways to reach dozens or hundreds instantly, and a PDF card is built to travel.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Broadcast list:</strong> send the card to many contacts at once, privately, as if messaging each one individually</li>\n<li><strong>WhatsApp Status:</strong> post the card so all your contacts can view and download it for 24 hours</li>\n<li><strong>Group share:</strong> drop it into relevant business, society or community groups</li>\n<li><strong>Forward:</strong> ask happy customers to forward it to their own contacts</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Because a PDF card can be forwarded endlessly, one send can spread across a whole network without any cost to you. A single share in an active group can reach people you would never meet in person. That reach is a benefit paper cards can never offer, as covered in <a href=\"/blog/benefits-pdf-visiting-cards-small-business\">benefits of PDF visiting cards for small businesses</a>.</p>\n<h2>Can I add my PDF card to my WhatsApp profile or link?</h2>\n<p>You can make your card the first thing new contacts receive. A common setup is a <strong>click-to-WhatsApp link</strong> or a QR code that opens a chat where you send the card straight away. Put that link in your Instagram bio, your Google listing, or your email signature to funnel enquiries into WhatsApp.</p>\n<p>You can also pin a message with the card in important chats so it never gets buried, or keep it in your Starred messages to resend in seconds during a busy day. If you use <strong>WhatsApp Business</strong>, add the card to your greeting message so every new enquiry receives it automatically, and save it as a quick reply for repeat sharing. These small setups mean your card does the introductions while you focus on the conversation.</p>\n<h2>What should the receiver do after opening the card?</h2>\n<p>Guide them with a short message so they act instead of just glancing and moving on. A card plus a clear line converts far better than a silent attachment, because most people need a tiny nudge to tap.</p>\n<table>\n<tr><th>If you want them to</th><th>Say this with the card</th></tr>\n<tr><td>Call you</td><td>\"Tap Call on the card to reach me directly.\"</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Pay you</td><td>\"Scan the UPI QR inside to pay instantly.\"</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Save your details</td><td>\"Tap the QR to save my contact in one tap.\"</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Follow you</td><td>\"Tap the Instagram button to see my work.\"</td></tr>\n</table>\n<p>A tiny prompt turns a shared file into a real conversation, a saved contact, or a payment. Match the instruction to whatever action matters most for that particular customer.</p>\n<h2>What if the buttons are not working for the receiver?</h2>\n<p>Ninety percent of the time, the card was sent as a photo instead of a Document. Resend it the correct way and the links come straight back to life. This is the first thing to check whenever a customer says nothing happens when they tap.</p>\n<p>Other quick checks: make sure they are opening the actual PDF file and not a screenshot they took, and that they are tapping directly on the button area rather than the surrounding space. Very old PDF viewers occasionally struggle, so suggest they open it in WhatsApp's built-in viewer or a standard reader like Adobe or their phone's default. It also helps to confirm they are on a reasonably recent version of WhatsApp, since very outdated apps handle documents poorly.</p>\n<p>If issues continue, MyCarda will help you troubleshoot on the <a href=\"/contact-us\">contact us</a> page. You can also preview correctly built, fully working cards on our <a href=\"/pdf-card-samples\">PDF card samples</a> page to compare against yours.</p>\n<div class=\"cta-box\"><p>Get a WhatsApp-ready PDF card with live call, chat and UPI buttons, delivered within 24 hours.</p><a href=\"/pricing\">Get Your PDF Card</a><a href=\"https://wa.me/919517722444\">WhatsApp Us</a></div>",
