    "content": "<div class=\"answer-block\"><strong>Quick answer:</strong> Great PDF business card design keeps it to one clean page, leads with your name and logo, uses readable fonts and brand colours, and makes every button obvious and tappable. Prioritise your top three actions (call, WhatsApp, UPI), add a scannable QR, and keep file size light so it opens fast on any phone.</div>\n<p>A good <strong>PDF business card design</strong> is not about cramming in every detail you can think of. It is about guiding one tap to the action that grows your business. Clean, clear and tappable beats busy and cluttered every single time.</p>\n<p>The best cards feel effortless to read and impossible to ignore, and they make the receiver's next step obvious.</p>\n<p>Here are ten practical PDF business card design tips, refined across thousands of MyCarda cards, to make yours look professional and actually convert.</p>\n<h2>1. Keep it to one clean page</h2>\n<p>A business card is a first impression, not a brochure. Fit everything onto <strong>one page</strong> so the receiver takes in your whole story at a glance, without scrolling or swiping. Multiple pages bury your buttons and slow people down, and a busy card makes even a good business look disorganised. If you genuinely have a lot to say, link out to your social profiles or website rather than stacking every detail on the card. Restraint reads as confidence.</p>\n<h2>2. Lead with your name, logo and photo</h2>\n<p>People trust faces and brands they can recognise. Place your <strong>name, logo and a clear headshot</strong> near the top so recognition is instant and personal. A photo especially builds trust for consultants, agents, doctors and freelancers, because customers like to see who they are dealing with. Keep the logo crisp and correctly sized so it never looks stretched or pixelated, and give your name the largest, boldest treatment on the card so it is the first thing anyone reads.</p>\n<h2>3. Choose readable fonts over fancy ones</h2>\n<p>Decorative fonts look creative in a preview and read terribly on a small phone screen. Pick <strong>clean, legible fonts</strong> and use just one or two across the whole card for a tidy, professional feel. Set a clear hierarchy: your name largest, your role or business medium, and contact details smaller but still comfortable to read. A quick test is to hold the card at arm's length on a phone; if a friend cannot read it easily, the font or the size is wrong and needs fixing.</p>\n<h2>4. Use your brand colours with plenty of white space</h2>\n<p>Colour sets the mood, but restraint is what sells. Use <strong>two or three brand colours</strong> at most and let generous white space breathe around your text and buttons. Crowded, edge-to-edge cards feel cheap, while spaced-out layouts feel premium and considered. Make sure your text contrasts strongly with the background so it stays readable in bright sunlight and in dark mode, where a low-contrast card can vanish. Good spacing also makes your buttons easier to tap accurately.</p>\n<h2>5. Make every button obvious and tappable</h2>\n<p>The whole point of a PDF card is the interaction, so the buttons must actually look like buttons. Give <strong>call, WhatsApp and UPI</strong> clear icons, short labels and enough spacing that a thumb cannot miss or hit the wrong one. Buttons that are too small or crammed together frustrate people and waste the format's biggest advantage. Aim for comfortable tap targets and a logical order, with your most important action first. See how these buttons are built on our <a href=\"/how-it-works\">how it works</a> page.</p>\n<h2>6. Prioritise your top three actions</h2>\n<p>Not every link deserves equal space. Decide the three actions that matter most to your business and give them the spotlight, then let everything else play a supporting role.</p>\n<table>\n<tr><th>Business type</th><th>Top 3 buttons to feature</th></tr>\n<tr><td>Shop or trader</td><td>UPI QR, Call, Maps</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Consultant or doctor</td><td>Call, WhatsApp, Book</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Creator or freelancer</td><td>Instagram, WhatsApp, Portfolio</td></tr>\n</table>\n<p>Feature the remaining links as smaller secondary buttons so the card stays focused and guides the eye toward the action you most want.</p>\n<h2>7. Add a scannable QR code</h2>\n<p>Not every situation is digital-to-digital. A <strong>scannable QR code</strong> lets someone save your contact or open your card from a printed poster, a shop wall, a packaging label, or another person's phone screen. Place it where it is easy to point a camera at, and keep enough plain, quiet space around it so cameras read it cleanly on the first try. A QR that is too small, too busy, or crammed into a corner often fails to scan, which defeats its purpose entirely.</p>\n<h2>8. Keep the file size light</h2>\n<p>A heavy PDF opens slowly and frustrates people on patchy networks, which is common across India. Compress your images sensibly so the card loads in about a second on any phone without looking blurry. A light file also sends faster on WhatsApp and is far less likely to be blocked or delayed for size in groups and broadcasts. Speed is a real part of good design even though it is invisible, because a card that opens instantly feels professional and a slow one feels broken.</p>\n<h2>9. Match the design to your industry</h2>\n<p>A doctor's card and a DJ's card should not look the same. Align your colours, tone and layout with what your <strong>industry</strong> expects, because customers read those signals instantly. Calm, clean and trustworthy suits medical and legal work; bold and vibrant suits creative fields; sharp and premium suits real estate and luxury services. Matching the mood makes your card feel credible to the exact audience you serve. Browse profession-specific styles on our <a href=\"/industries\">industries</a> page for inspiration before you finalise your look.</p>\n<h2>10. Test on a real phone before sharing</h2>\n<p>Always preview your finished card on an actual phone, not just a laptop screen. Check that <strong>every button works</strong>, the text is readable, the colours look right, and the QR scans on the first try. Tap through each link yourself and confirm the call button dials the correct number and the WhatsApp button opens your chat. A quick two-minute test catches wrong numbers or dead links before a single customer ever sees them. Compare your result against polished examples on our <a href=\"/pdf-card-samples\">PDF card samples</a> page.</p>\n<p>Want these ten principles applied for you without the guesswork? MyCarda handles the design so your card looks professional from the first day. If you are still deciding on a plan, read <a href=\"/blog/digital-visiting-card-price-india\">digital visiting card price in India</a> to pick the right one, and see the full <a href=\"/pdf-digital-business-card\">PDF digital business card</a> feature list before you order.</p>\n<div class=\"cta-box\"><p>Let our team design a clean, high-converting PDF card for you, delivered within 24 hours.</p><a href=\"/pricing\">Get Your PDF Card</a><a href=\"https://wa.me/919517722444\">WhatsApp Us</a></div>",
