    "content": "<div class=\"answer-block\"><strong>Quick answer:</strong> To add a UPI payment QR code to your PDF business card, share your UPI ID with MyCarda, and we embed a scannable QR that lets anyone pay you instantly via Google Pay, PhonePe, or Paytm, right from your card. It works on every device with no app, starting at ₹99.</div>\n<p>Getting paid should be the easiest part of running a business, yet chasing payments wastes hours every week. Adding a <strong>UPI payment QR code to your PDF business card</strong> turns your card into a payment counter that customers can tap and pay in seconds.</p>\n<p>The problem with sharing bank details or generating a fresh payment link each time is friction, and friction loses payments. A permanent UPI QR on your card removes every step between a willing customer and a completed payment.</p>\n<p>In this tutorial you will learn exactly how a UPI QR works on a PDF card, the step-by-step setup, and the best practices to collect payments faster.</p>\n<h2>What is a UPI payment QR code on a PDF card?</h2>\n<p>A <strong>UPI payment QR code</strong> is a scannable image linked to your UPI ID. When a customer scans it with any UPI app, the payment screen opens pre-filled with your details, so they just enter the amount and pay. On a PDF card, this QR sits permanently, ready whenever you need to collect money.</p>\n<p>It works with every major UPI app in India, so customers use whatever they already have.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Google Pay</strong>, <strong>PhonePe</strong>, <strong>Paytm</strong>, BHIM, and bank UPI apps.</li>\n<li>No card machine, no payment gateway fees.</li>\n<li>Direct bank-to-bank transfer to your account.</li>\n<li>Works instantly, 24x7, including holidays.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Because your card is a universal PDF, the QR scans cleanly from any screen or printout. Learn the format basics in our guide on <a href=\"/blog/what-is-pdf-digital-business-card\">what a PDF digital business card is</a>.</p>\n<h2>Why add a payment QR code to your business card?</h2>\n<p>A payment QR turns your <strong>digital business card</strong> into a point of sale. Instead of sending bank details or a link, you share one card that lets customers pay on the spot, which dramatically improves how fast and how often you get paid.</p>\n<p>It also looks professional and builds trust. A customer who can pay you cleanly through a branded card feels reassured, especially for advances, deposits, and consultation fees.</p>\n<table>\n<tr><th>Without QR</th><th>With UPI QR on card</th></tr>\n<tr><td>Share bank details manually</td><td>Customer scans and pays instantly</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Generate a new link each time</td><td>One permanent QR, always ready</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Payment delays and follow-ups</td><td>Immediate, on-the-spot payment</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Risk of typos in account numbers</td><td>Details pre-filled, error-free</td></tr>\n</table>\n<p>This benefits doctors, freelancers, shopkeepers, and service providers alike. See who else uses it on our <a href=\"/industries\">industries page</a>.</p>\n<p>UPI has become India's default way to pay, with billions of transactions every month across small shops and large businesses. Customers now expect a QR to be available, and its absence can feel outdated. Putting a UPI QR on your card meets that expectation and removes any excuse a customer might have to delay paying you.</p>\n<h2>How do I add a UPI QR code to my PDF card? (Step by step)</h2>\n<p>Adding a payment QR to your <strong>PDF business card</strong> with MyCarda takes minutes on your side. Here is the exact process from start to finish.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Choose your plan:</strong> pick a plan on our <a href=\"/pricing\">pricing page</a> that includes the payment QR feature.</li>\n<li><strong>Share your UPI ID:</strong> send us your UPI handle (for example, yourname@okhdfcbank) via WhatsApp or the <a href=\"/contact-us\">contact page</a>.</li>\n<li><strong>Send your card details:</strong> provide your name, business, logo, and other links you want on the card.</li>\n<li><strong>We generate the QR:</strong> our team creates a scannable UPI QR tied to your ID and places it on your card.</li>\n<li><strong>Review the draft:</strong> we send you the PDF card to check the QR and details.</li>\n<li><strong>Test the payment:</strong> scan the QR yourself with a UPI app to confirm it opens your payment screen.</li>\n<li><strong>Approve and go live:</strong> once confirmed, your card is ready to share and collect payments.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The whole card is delivered within <strong>24 hours</strong>. See the full workflow on our <a href=\"/how-it-works\">how it works</a> page.</p>\n<h2>Is a UPI QR code on a PDF card safe?</h2>\n<p>Yes. A <strong>UPI QR code</strong> only carries your receiving details, so scanning it lets people pay you, never withdraw from you. There is no risk in displaying it publicly, which is why shops across India print UPI QRs at the counter.</p>\n<p>Payments go directly bank-to-bank through India's secure UPI network, regulated by NPCI. You receive instant notifications in your UPI app for every payment, so you always have a clear record.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The QR only receives money; it cannot debit your account.</li>\n<li>Every transaction is logged in your UPI app history.</li>\n<li>No sensitive bank details are exposed on the card.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For extra clarity, always verify the payer's name and the exact amount in your app before delivering goods or services. Be cautious of anyone who shows only a screenshot of a supposed payment, a genuine transfer always appears in your own UPI app history within seconds, and that is the record you should trust.</p>\n<h2>What are the best practices for a payment QR on your card?</h2>\n<p>To get the most from your <strong>payment QR code</strong>, place and use it thoughtfully. A few small choices make payments smoother and reduce confusion for customers.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Place it prominently:</strong> keep the QR visible so it is easy to find.</li>\n<li><strong>Label it clearly:</strong> add text like Scan to Pay via UPI.</li>\n<li><strong>Show your UPI name:</strong> so customers confirm they are paying the right person.</li>\n<li><strong>Test before sharing:</strong> always scan it once yourself first.</li>\n<li><strong>Keep a backup:</strong> mention your number in case a customer needs to confirm.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You can also pair the QR with a click-to-call and WhatsApp button so customers can reach you if they have any payment query. Browse card layouts with payment QRs on our <a href=\"/pdf-card-samples\">PDF card samples</a> page.</p>\n<h2>How much does a PDF card with a payment QR cost?</h2>\n<p>The payment QR feature is included in MyCarda's plans at one-time pricing with no subscription or per-transaction fee from us. You pay once and collect unlimited payments.</p>\n<table>\n<tr><th>Plan</th><th>Price (one-time)</th><th>Payment QR included</th></tr>\n<tr><td>Started</td><td>₹99</td><td>Yes</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Business</td><td>₹499</td><td>Yes, with more features</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Premium</td><td>₹999</td><td>Yes, with premium design</td></tr>\n</table>\n<p>Beyond payments, the same card carries your click-to-call, WhatsApp, Google Maps, and social links, so it works as a complete business card and a payment counter in one. That combination is why professionals across India choose a single MyCarda card over juggling separate tools for contact and collection.</p>\n<p>See full inclusions on our <a href=\"/pricing\">pricing page</a> and the complete feature set on our <a href=\"/pdf-digital-business-card\">PDF digital business card</a> page. With 12,500+ happy customers and a 4.9/5 rating, MyCarda makes getting paid effortless for Indian businesses.</p>\n<div class=\"cta-box\"><p>Turn your business card into a payment counter, add a UPI QR and get paid instantly, delivered within 24 hours.</p><a href=\"/pricing\">Get Your PDF Card</a><a href=\"https://wa.me/919517722444\">WhatsApp Us</a></div>",
